As you lay helpless on your deathbed you see the reaper standing over you. ‚ÄúWhat is it grand(ma/pa)?‚Äù, asks your grandniece as you let out your last gurgled gasp. One by one he sends people to Heaven or to Hell. You know you‚Äôre going to Hell, I mean, who isn‚Äôt right?

When you reach the end of the line you look Michael in the eyes. You‚Äôre going to hell so you might as well ask: ‚ÄúDid you touch those ki‚Ä¶‚Äù, before you can finish your question Michael kisses you on the lips. Suddenly you‚Äôre floating up towards a beautiful sunny sky. This isn‚Äôt Hell, this is Heaven! This song plays as you ascend toward the pearly gates.

Not to be a bummer but all of the best songs are about breakups. Go for whatever vibe you want: crying on the bathroom floor, rebounding at the club, murdering your cheating husband, etc. 

In memory of Harry Styles and Olivia Wilde, may they rest in peace.

name: Longing for ‚ÄúYou‚Äù
description:
You get to the party and see her across the room. She radiates light and goodness in a city full of vapid and uninspired girls. You knew she would be here, You know everything about her, You're here to protect her. You're meant to be, even if she doesn't know it yet. You've been called a stalker before but, people just don't understand You. You're just one of the good guys that really CARES!

This song is playing as time stops and you replay your future lives together as you approach her.

name: Esoteric Earworms
description:
Pick a song that scores as high as possible on both of these measures: 
1) Esoteric: a song no one else has heard before. It should be brand new to as many people as possible.
2. Earworm: A song that's catchy as fuck, even obnoxiously catchy. A song that gets stuck in your head for days and comes to mind easily, even if it's been years since you've actually listened to it.

name: Solidarity Forever
description:
Protest songs that make you feel something in your gut. You know something is wrong with the world and this song speaks to it perfectly. From the big energy Fuck toys that you‚Äôd play on the front lines to slower songs that highlight injustices through just your headphones, whichever cause you want new or old. Solidarity for all of it!

** Except for these songs. They‚Äôre all great but they are disqualified bc we can all do better.

name: The Beat Goes On

From pop rock to rap to techno to esoteric instrumental tracks and everything in between. The only rule is this: the percussion has to drive and be interwoven throughout: an 8 minute solo in the later half of a song isn't it.

name: Extraterrestrial Dance Party
description:
It is 2005 and you're home alone in your room listening to your iPod on your boom box. A blue light renders you incapacitated and you are pulled up into an alien spaceship. You wake up to tied to a table and see them inspecting your boom box. The aux cord is still attached, THIS is your chance to escape. You must play an "other worldly/futuristic" song that will force the aliens into a feverish, uncontrollable dance so you can make your escape. 

Doesn't have to be from 2005.

name: The Metamorphosis
description:
Submit a song that showcases dynamic transformations from beginning to end. Whether it's a change in tempo, instrumentation, or mood, I want to hear tracks that take listeners on a journey and evolve into something unexpected. From subtle shifts to dramatic transformations, show us how songs can evolve and surprise us.
No Stairway to Heaven, no Space Oddity, no Bohemian Rhapsody, no Baba O‚ÄôRiley.

name: Melodic Tracks
description: The beat of the song must not be audible, meaning no songs with drums, beatboxing, or traditional percussion instruments. Instruments like the piano, which are technically percussion, are allowed. The requirement is that the rhythm section (not rhythm itself) must be absent from the song.

name: Atypical Instrumentation
description:
Looking for songs that feature uncommon or strange instruments, non-standard usage of instruments, or idiosyncratic ways of playing instruments. What counts as strange/uncommon is up to you, but like, a band with synthesizers don't count. Your pick has to have been released between 2014 and now. 

Pop music with weird tropical cuica samples absolutely counts.

name: Locals Only!
description:
Time to shout out your buddies band! Do you have a cousin who's a DJ, does your boyfriends bff play in a klezmer band, are you in love with a weird punk band that plays in a swamp down under? This playlist is for them!
The rules:
1) You must know someone in the band 
2) if you don't know anyone in the band, they have to be based in the city/nearest largest city you live in (or have lived in very recently)
3) play count of the song has to be 50K or less (or if it's more- not in the top 5 songs)
